2017-2018 Salinity in SFE

Chelsey Wegener

10/15/2020

Graphing all the salinity data from 2017-2018. I’ve removed outliers and combined them all into one data set.

Convert to date

sal$date<-as.Date(sal$date, format = c("%Y-%m-%d"))

Subset data by site

cc<-subset(sal, sal$site == "China Camp")
eos<-subset(sal, sal$site == "Tiburon")
rb<-subset(sal, sal$site == "Richardson Bay")
fp<-subset(sal, sal$site == "Fort Point")

Graph

cc1<-ggplot(data = cc, mapping = aes(x = date, y = salinity, color=salinity)) + geom_point()+ylim(0,35)  +stat_smooth(colour="green")+ggtitle("China Camp") +  theme(plot.title = element_text(size = 12, face = "plain")) +theme(axis.text=element_text(size=12),axis.title=element_text(size=12,face="plain")) + ylab("Salinity") + xlab("") + theme(panel.grid.major = element_blank(), panel.grid.minor = element_blank(), panel.background = element_blank(), axis.line = element_line(colour = "black"))

eos1<-ggplot(data = eos, mapping = aes(x = date, y = salinity, color=salinity)) + geom_point() +ylim(0,35)  +stat_smooth(colour="green")+ggtitle("Tiburon") +  theme(plot.title = element_text(size = 12, face = "plain")) +theme(axis.text=element_text(size=12),axis.title=element_text(size=12,face="plain")) + ylab("Salinity") + xlab("") + theme(panel.grid.major = element_blank(), panel.grid.minor = element_blank(), panel.background = element_blank(), axis.line = element_line(colour = "black"))

rb1<-ggplot(data = rb, mapping = aes(x = date, y = salinity, color=salinity)) + geom_point()+ylim(0,35)   +stat_smooth(colour="green")+ggtitle("Richardson Bay") +  theme(plot.title = element_text(size = 12, face = "plain")) +theme(axis.text=element_text(size=12),axis.title=element_text(size=12,face="plain")) + ylab("Salinity") + xlab("") + theme(panel.grid.major = element_blank(), panel.grid.minor = element_blank(), panel.background = element_blank(), axis.line = element_line(colour = "black"))

fp1<-ggplot(data = fp, mapping = aes(x = date, y = salinity, color=salinity)) + geom_point()+ylim(0,35)   +stat_smooth(colour="green")+ggtitle("Fort Point") +  theme(plot.title = element_text(size = 12, face = "plain")) +theme(axis.text=element_text(size=12),axis.title=element_text(size=12,face="plain")) + ylab("Salinity") + xlab("") + theme(panel.grid.major = element_blank(), panel.grid.minor = element_blank(), panel.background = element_blank(), axis.line = element_line(colour = "black"))

Stack and annotate

sal_graph<-ggarrange(cc1, eos1, rb1, fp1, ncol = 1, nrow = 4)
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'gam' and formula 'y ~ s(x, bs = "cs")'
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'gam' and formula 'y ~ s(x, bs = "cs")'
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'gam' and formula 'y ~ s(x, bs = "cs")'
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'gam' and formula 'y ~ s(x, bs = "cs")'
annotate_figure(sal_graph,
                top = text_grob("Salinity", color = "black", face = "plain", size = 14), left = text_grob("Salinity", color = "black", rot = 90, size=12))
